# ========================================
# CANONICAL SEO REDIRECTS (APEX PRIMARY DOMAIN)
# ========================================
# Target: https://gappsy.com/<path>/
# Netlify's site config has gappsy.com (apex) set as the primary custom
# domain, which makes Netlify auto-redirect www.gappsy.com -> gappsy.com
# at the platform level. This file previously forced the opposite
# direction (apex -> www), and the two redirect rules fought each other,
# producing an infinite gappsy.com <-> www.gappsy.com redirect loop that
# took the whole site down. We enforce apex as the primary domain here to
# match Netlify's actual configuration.

# Step 1: Redirect www and HTTP to the canonical apex HTTPS URL
http://gappsy.com/*  https://gappsy.com/:splat  301!
http://www.gappsy.com/*  https://gappsy.com/:splat  301!
https://www.gappsy.com/*  https://gappsy.com/:splat  301!

# Step 2: Add trailing slash for page URLs only (exclude files with extensions and API routes)
# This regex matches paths without dots (files) and without trailing slash
# Note: /api/* rules above use 200! force-rewrite which takes priority, but this exclusion is belt-and-suspenders
/api/*  /api/:splat  200!
/([^.?]+[^/])  /$1/  301!

