# Prerendered tool pages: deliberately NO explicit redirect rule here.
# dist/tools/{slug}/index.html is served by Netlify's default static-file
# precedence (an exact file match always wins over any redirect rule,
# without needing "force"), so a valid slug resolves correctly with zero
# rewrite risk. Both explicit-rule variants tried here (named :slug, then
# splat *) misbehaved on production for the missing-target case — one
# 404'd nonexistent tool slugs instead of falling through to the SPA, the
# other broke the bare /tools listing page too. Relying on native
# resolution avoids that whole failure class: no rule to misfire, so an
# unmatched slug (or the bare /tools / /tools/ listing, which also has no
# generated file) falls straight through to the SPA fallback below.

# 4. SPA fallback
/*  /index.html 200
